    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 16,
        "summary": "It is better to get wisdom than gold\u2014Pride goes before destruction\u2014The gray hair of the righteous person is a crown of glory.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The preparations of the heart in man, and the answer of the tongue, is from the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 16:16 (16\u201317); 32:6.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 100:5 (5\u20138).",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes; but the Lord weigheth the spirits.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 30:12.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 17:6; Prov. 21:2.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Commit thy works unto the Lord, and thy thoughts shall be established.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 55:22; Matt. 6:25; Philip. 4:6.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Motivations.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord hath made all things for himself: yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Every one that is proud in heart is an abomination to the Lord: though hand join in hand, he shall not be unpunished.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:40.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "By mercy and truth iniquity is purged: and by the fear of the Lord men depart from evil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 1:17 (16\u201317); Job 1:1.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 20:26.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 136:21.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When a man's ways please the Lord, he maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 34:24.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 1:9. TG\u00a0Peace; Peace of God.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Better is a little with righteousness than great revenues without right.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 32:12 (12\u201313).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man's heart deviseth his way: but the Lord directeth his steps.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 2:16 (16\u201325).",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A divine sentence is in the lips of the king: his mouth transgresseth not in judgment.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A just weight and balance are the Lord's: all the weights of the bag are his work.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 828
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is an abomination to kings to commit wickedness: for the throne is established by righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 23:9 (8\u201310); 29:17 (17\u201319).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Righteous lips are the delight of kings; and they love him that speaketh right.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wrath of a king is as messengers of death: but a wise man will pacify it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the light of the king's countenance is life; and his favour is as a cloud of the latter rain.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "How much better is it to get wisdom than gold! and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver!",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Objectives.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The highway of the upright is to depart from evil: he that keepeth his way preserveth his soul.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Pride goeth before destruction, and an haughty spirit before a fall.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pride.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haughtiness.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Better it is to be of an humble spirit with the lowly, than to divide the spoil with the proud.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contrite Heart; Poor in Spirit.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that handleth a matter wisely shall find good: and whoso trusteth in the Lord, happy is he.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 58:27 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust in God.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Happiness.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wise in heart shall be called prudent: and the sweetness of the lips increaseth learning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Understanding is a wellspring of life unto him that hath it: but the instruction of fools is folly.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The heart of the wise teacheth his mouth, and addeth learning to his lips.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Pleasant words are as an honeycomb, sweet to the soul, and health to the bones.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is a way that seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 28:7 (7\u20139); Alma 30:17 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that laboureth laboureth for himself; for his mouth craveth it of him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "An ungodly man diggeth up evil: and in his lips there is as a burning fire.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "James 3:6 (1\u201313).",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A froward man soweth strife: and a whisperer separateth chief friends.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A violent man enticeth his neighbour, and leadeth him into the way that is not good.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He shutteth his eyes to devise froward things: moving his lips he bringeth evil to pass.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The hoary head is a crown of glory, if it be found in the way of righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0The gray hair of old age. Prov. 20:29.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is slow to anger is better than the mighty; and he that ruleth his spirit than he that taketh a city.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The lot is cast into the lap; but the whole disposing thereof is of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 18:18; 1\u00a0Ne. 3:11; D&C 102:34.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}